{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:59:18.744048+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's the complete breakdown of every subcommand registered in `gita/cmds.json`:\n\n| # | Subcommand | Underlying `git` command | `allow_all` | `disable_async` |\n|---|-----------|--------------------------|:-----------:|:---------------:|\n| 1 | **`br`** | `git branch -vv` | — | — |\n| 2 | **`clean`** | `git clean -dfx` | — | — |\n| 3 | **`diff`** | `git diff` | — | — |\n| 4 | **`difftool`** | `git difftool` | — | ✅ |\n| 5 | **`fetch`** | `git fetch` | ✅ | — |\n| 6 | **`last`** | `git log -1 HEAD` | — | — |\n| 7 | **`lo`** | `git log --oneline -7` | ✅ | — |\n| 8 | **`log`** | `git log` | — | ✅ |\n| 9 | **`merge`** | `git merge @{u}` | — | — |\n| 10 | **`mergetool`** | `git mergetool` | — | ✅ |\n| 11 | **`patch`** | `git format-patch HEAD~` | — | — |\n| 12 | **`pull`** | `git pull` | ✅ | — |\n| 13 | **`push`** | `git push` | ✅ | — |\n| 14 | **`rebase`** | `git rebase` | — | — |\n| 15 | **`reflog`** | `git reflog` | — | — |\n| 16 | **`remote`** | `git remote -v` | — | — |\n| 17 | **`reset`** | `git reset` | — | — |\n| 18 | **`show`** | `git show` | — | ✅ |\n| 19 | **`stash`** | `git stash` | — | — |\n| 20 | **`stat`** | `git diff --stat` | ✅ | — |\n| 21 | **`st`** | `git status` | ✅ | — |\n| 22 | **`tag`** | `git tag -n` | — | — |\n\n### Special flags summary\n\n**`allow_all: true`** (6 subcommands) — These can be applied across *all* repos at once:\n- `fetch` · `lo` · `pull` · `push` · `stat` · `st`\n\n**`disable_async: true`** (4 subcommands) — These run synchronously (serially) instead of in parallel:\n- `difftool` · `log` · `mergetool` · `show`\n\nThis makes intuitive sense: the `disable_async` entries are commands that either produce interactive output (difftool/mergetool) or produce verbose output that would be unintelligible when interleaved (full `log`, `show`). The `allow_all` entries are the everyday network/status operations you'd want to fan out across every managed repo in one shot.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 743, "prompt_tokens": 7162, "total_tokens": 7905, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 28, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6400, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.00033264, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001246, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00020804}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780873150-KyLjFE0wR88gW08qkyCR", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea44f-be6f-7ea2-8eb7-600e4599e201-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7162, "output_tokens": 743, "total_tokens": 7905, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 6400}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 28}}}}]}}}
